{"type":"message","id":"a594814e","parentId":"1b4f9953","timestamp":"2026-04-21T04:46:45.020Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The gateway processes are running but not listening on any TCP port. This is very strange. Let me try a different approach - use the openclaw CLI to check the status.\n\nActually, I think the issue might be that the gateway is using a Unix socket instead of a TCP port, or it's configured differently. Let me check the gateway config more carefully.\n\nActually, wait. Looking at the config again: `\"bind\": \"loopback\"` and `\"port\": 18789`. This should bind to 127.0.0.1:18789. But maybe the config is not being read properly?\n\nLet me check if the config file is valid by running `openclaw doctor`.","thinkingSignature":"34cef2a7ab8bf4bec8d4661017650224f2fa43233250e7e6c2636a222822a4c9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_impi9c32wqmg_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sshpass -p '0zDxl1N36E(p@J' ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no root@161.248.81.138 'timeout 15 openclaw doctor 2>&1 | head -30'","yieldMs":16000,"timeout":20}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":84,"output":234,"cacheRead":75833,"cacheWrite":412,"totalTokens":76563,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776746798736,"responseId":"06363430797788a1bedeb9c9f0062a1c"}}
