{"type":"message","id":"0475c519","parentId":"9052b365","timestamp":"2026-04-21T04:47:17.678Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The openclaw doctor command is also producing no output and getting killed. There might be a fundamental issue with the SSH connection timing out or the process timing out. \n\nLet me try a very different approach. Instead of trying to debug the gateway remotely, let me just verify the core setup is done and let the user test the Telegram bot themselves.\n\nActually, I think the issue might be that the VPS has a process limit or the SSH commands keep timing out. Let me try to do things more quickly and in fewer commands.\n\nActually, the gateway IS running (I can see the processes). The issue is just that port 18789 is not being listened on. Let me check if maybe the gateway is using a different config file or the port is blocked.Wait, I just realized something. Looking at the config-health.json from earlier:\n\n\nThe config file size doesn't match what I uploaded, so there might be multiple config versions or the file got overwritten. I need to verify which config the running gateway is actually using.","thinkingSignature":"87d284d618221e24d6e65aa735f70b6f0402a2f68e1bf0e7d15ee79fad39dead"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_f4p47k7lyu3k_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sshpass -p '0zDxl1N36E(p@J' ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no root@161.248.81.138 'ls -la /root/.openclaw/openclaw.json && wc -c /root/.openclaw/openclaw.json'","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":89,"output":296,"cacheRead":76262,"cacheWrite":343,"totalTokens":76990,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776746829300,"responseId":"0636344e5a94492e6052738eb7aa99da"}}
