{"type":"message","id":"941813e0","parentId":"ffc0da0e","timestamp":"2026-04-21T04:51:49.117Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, the environment doesn't show OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH. Maybe it's reading from the default location. Let me check if maybe there's a systemd service file that sets different parameters.\n\nActually, let me just try to check if the gateway is working by connecting to the Telegram bot. If the bot responds, then the gateway is working even if the port isn't listening via TCP.\n\nActually, wait. I just realized something. The old gateway (PID 2423 from April 2) - that was running when I first connected to the VPS. It was already installed and configured. Maybe the issue is that my new config is conflicting with the existing setup.\n\nLet me check if the old openclaw.json is still there somehow, or if the system is using a different config.\n\n\nActually, let me step back and try a simpler approach. The real issue might be that the gateway is running but silently failing due to config problems. Instead of debugging the port, I should test whether the Telegram bot actually responds—that would tell me if the gateway is functioning despite the port issue.","thinkingSignature":"9709a15e5808227b577342157ad2507a8e44bc2fd311b62188ca92eab3eb8e96"},{"type":"text","text":"Gateway đang chạy nhưng không mở port. Test Telegram bot trực tiếp:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nzp6utc4p11v_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s https://api.telegram.org/bot8605080868:AAFFvDZs3YwWfxaLgW7Lgj42ANwyFIzmFT8/getUpdates | python3 -m json.tool 2>/dev/null | head -20","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":127,"output":329,"cacheRead":83697,"cacheWrite":521,"totalTokens":84674,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776747099964,"responseId":"0636355da12c31e416f6f39a8a4da86b"}}
