{"type":"message","id":"e2764eb1","parentId":"ea825dc6","timestamp":"2026-04-21T04:51:59.151Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Telegram bot is accessible but there are no updates. This means the bot is connected to Telegram's servers but there are no pending messages.\n\nThe fact that the bot is connected to Telegram's servers is actually a good sign - it means the openclaw gateway is probably working! The issue might just be that the gateway is listening on a different mechanism (not TCP) or it's using WebSocket/Long Polling to connect to Telegram, which doesn't require a publicly accessible TCP port.\n\nWait, but I can't access port 18789 from outside. The gateway is on a VPS with a public IP. Let me check if maybe the issue is that the gateway is only binding to loopback and not to the public IP.\n \nSo the bot is actually connected to Telegram's servers through an outbound connection from the VPS, which means the gateway is functioning properly. The real issue is just that port 18789 isn't accessible from outside - likely because it's bound to loopback instead of the public interface. I should verify whether the port is actually listening or if there's a configuration issue preventing external access.","thinkingSignature":"13f6720f794042734403febe407ee4716ffb599a8a9852adb9012340f101b4b7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ckqvibnpqfzb_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sshpass -p '0zDxl1N36E(p@J' ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no root@161.248.81.138 'curl -sv http://127.0.0.1:18789/ 2>&1 | head -15'","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":89,"output":312,"cacheRead":84041,"cacheWrite":571,"totalTokens":85013,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776747110030,"responseId":"06363567e4f32cabd6d7e47f81e13c0a"}}
