{"type":"message","id":"172c5eed","parentId":"da8373cb","timestamp":"2026-04-21T04:55:40.975Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The config-health.json now shows the new config (bytes: 33644, but I uploaded 28281... wait, that's a different size). Let me check - the file on disk has 28281 bytes, but the health shows 33644 bytes. This means the health system is seeing a different file! Maybe the VPS has some kind of config override or the file was modified after I uploaded it.\n\nWait, actually the issue might be that the old gateway processes (from the previous invalid config) are still running and they keep restarting with the old config. The new gateway processes (348162, 348301, 348321) were started after I killed the old ones, but they might be loading a cached version of the config.\n \nThe hash in the health check is `5abbb64de80f0674392bb4d5ce376d950c05e35beefefdc4816f488bb368f58b`, but I'm seeing conflicting byte counts - the health shows 33644 bytes while the actual file is 28281 bytes. Something's not adding up here.\n\nLet me think through this: the gateway process is clearly running and connecting to Telegram, but it's not producing any logs and port 18789 isn't listening. Maybe the logging is configured to output somewhere else entirely, or perhaps the process is just running silently without writing to file. Or maybe the real issue is that the gateway was already running on the VPS before I got involved, started by some automated process that I'm not seeing, and it's using its own startup configuration that I haven't touched.\n\nI should check if there's a systemd service or supervisor script that auto-starts the gateway, since that would explain why the old config keeps reloading even after I update it.","thinkingSignature":"365723d043eb55a20008157a4e5a241a1a42ab00892c2100c239471f280dd638"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_71hkd0k96g90_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sshpass -p '0zDxl1N36E(p@J' ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no root@161.248.81.138 'systemctl list-units | grep openclaw && echo \"---\" && ls /etc/systemd/system/ | grep openclaw && echo \"---\" && cat /etc/supervisor/conf.d/*.conf 2>/dev/null | grep -i openclaw'","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":279,"output":480,"cacheRead":92653,"cacheWrite":493,"totalTokens":93905,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776747328349,"responseId":"0636364134fe39121c9853c3a4936fd5"}}
