{"type":"message","id":"909d4055","parentId":"3077e3b7","timestamp":"2026-04-21T05:19:51.478Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pairing code doesn't seem to be stored anywhere. The `openclaw pairing approve` command hangs, which might mean it's waiting for the gateway to respond but the gateway isn't responding to the CLI's requests.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The `openclaw` CLI might be using IPC (inter-process communication) to talk to the gateway, rather than HTTP. Let me check if there's a UNIX socket or named pipe.\n\nActually, looking at the logs more carefully - the openclaw gateway process seems to be running fine. The issue is that the CLI can't communicate with it. Maybe the CLI tries to connect to the gateway via a WebSocket connection that fails.\n \nI could try accessing the gateway's control UI directly through its web interface instead, or maybe configure it to listen on all interfaces so I can reach it from outside. But first, let me verify whether the pairing code is even persisting in the Telegram channel storage.","thinkingSignature":"5e09fe28297bba52b0f62695aa653c7cdc112fc7163159bf0f7bfdcb104a1426"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hs2w8i8wbikx_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sshpass -p '0zDxl1N36E(p@J' ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no root@161.248.81.138 'find /root/.openclaw -name \"*.json\" | xargs grep -l \"telegram\\|pairing\" 2>/dev/null | grep -v node_modules | head -10'","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":173,"output":297,"cacheRead":98464,"cacheWrite":358,"totalTokens":99292,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776748783430,"responseId":"06363bf089d252dc79f15b193f1d627e"}}
