{"type":"message","id":"3cec860e","parentId":"1310901c","timestamp":"2026-04-21T05:20:00.293Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"These are just session JSON files, not pairing data. Let me check if there's a specific storage for Telegram channel data or pairing data.\n\nLet me try a completely different approach. Instead of using the CLI, let me try to use the Telegram bot API to directly communicate with the bot and see if there's a pending pairing request.\n\nActually, wait - let me re-read the issue. The user sent `openclaw pairing approve telegram 7H8EP2CZ`. This is a command to approve a pairing request that came from the Telegram channel. The pairing code `7H8EP2CZ` was generated when the user tried to pair their Telegram account with the bot.\n\nThe fact that the command hangs suggests the gateway isn't responding to the CLI. This might be because the gateway is using a protocol that the CLI doesn't understand, or the CLI is trying to connect via a specific mechanism that fails.\n \nI should check if there's a REST API endpoint for pairing, or try connecting to the gateway's WebSocket directly instead.","thinkingSignature":"00395c51f721193444213e3cd68305b35644dfaf2e9969bb4dc26b2abb0a0f30"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9kk0ko06jy40_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sshpass -p '0zDxl1N36E(p@J' ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no root@161.248.81.138 'timeout 3 curl -s http://127.0.0.1:18789/api/ 2>&1; echo \"---\"; timeout 3 curl -s http://127.0.0.1:18789/api/v1/ 2>&1'","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":242,"output":330,"cacheRead":98681,"cacheWrite":549,"totalTokens":99802,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776748791909,"responseId":"06363bf98fa98b49180dbf3e336158a4"}}
