{"type":"compaction","id":"890cb387","parentId":"0ef95e40","timestamp":"2026-04-21T07:30:18.455Z","summary":"## Goal\n1. Setup OpenClaw agent ecosystem on new VPS (161.248.81.138) — clone current config with new tokens\n2. Setup OpenClaw on another new VPS (103.253.21.137) — **BLOCKED: SSH auth failed**\n3. Approve Telegram pairing for VPS1 bot (@tieuvydev_bot)\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- 1 shared Telegram bot token for ALL agents (no per-agent bots)\n- No group configuration — DM-only (`dmPolicy: \"pairing\"`)\n- API keys/tokens provided by user (not copied from current machine)\n- Do not push agent ecosystem to GitLab\n\n## Progress\n\n### Done\n- [x] Checked VPS1 disk space — 34GB disk at 98%, cleaned ~1.5GB (APT cache, old snap revisions, journal logs, btmp)\n- [x] VPS1 SSH verified: `ssh root@161.248.81.138` / `0zDxl1N36E(p@J`, Ubuntu 22.04\n- [x] VPS1 installed OpenClaw 2026.4.15 via `npm install -g openclaw@2026.4.15`\n- [x] VPS1 created directory structure: `/root/.openclaw/{agents,skills,mcp-servers,workspaces2,...}`\n- [x] VPS1 uploaded `openclaw.json` config (38 agents, single Telegram bot, new tokens)\n- [x] VPS1 copied all 38 skills via `rsync` (3.3MB)\n- [x] VPS1 copied all agents directories via `rsync` (57MB including sessions)\n- [x] VPS1 copied MCP servers (gitlab, figma, confluence, mcp-gitlab, mcp-stitch-key)\n- [x] VPS1 created workspace directories for all 38 agents\n- [x] VPS1 created `/root/start-openclaw.sh` startup script with all env vars\n- [x] VPS1 configured systemd service at `/etc/systemd/system/openclaw-gateway.service` with all env vars\n- [x] VPS1 cleared old `config-health.json` to force reload\n- [x] VPS1 restarted gateway via `systemctl restart openclaw-gateway`\n- [x] VPS1 verified gateway listening on `127.0.0.1:18789` ✅ and serving HTTP 200 ✅\n- [x] VPS1 Telegram bot verified: `@tieuvydev_bot` (token `8605080868:AAFFvDZs3YwWfxaLgW7Lgj42ANwyFIzmFT8`) — valid and connected ✅\n- [x] VPS1 env vars added to `/root/.bashrc` for persistence\n- [x] Telegram pairing code `7H8EP2CZ` attempted — **expired/not found** on both machines\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Telegram pairing for VPS1 — waiting for user to generate new code from `@tieuvydev_bot`\n- [ ] VPS2 setup (103.253.21.137) — **SSH blocked**\n\n### Blocked\n- **VPS2 SSH auth failed**: Server rejects password auth (`Permission denied (keyboard-interactive)`). Password `38afG1FL!D5o[` contains special chars `!`, `[`, `]` — possibly wrong or server only accepts SSH key. User needs to confirm credentials.\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Removed `match` key from agent configs**: VPS OpenClaw 2026.4.15 rejects `\"match\"` in `agents.list[].match` — removed from config\n- **Removed `routing` top-level key**: VPS version also rejects top-level `routing` key — removed from config\n- **Systemd manages gateway on VPS**: Instead of manual `nohup`, configured `/etc/systemd/system/openclaw-gateway.service` with all env vars for auto-restart\n- **Single Telegram bot**: All 38 agents use same `@tieuvydev_bot` via `dmPolicy: \"pairing\"` — no per-agent bots, no groups\n\n## Next Steps\n1. **User to verify VPS2 SSH credentials** — provide correct password or SSH private key\n2. **VPS1 Telegram pairing**: User gets new code from `@tieuvydev_bot` (send `/start` or `/pair`) and shares new code\n3. **Once VPS2 credentials resolved**: Repeat same setup process as VPS1\n\n## Critical Context\n\n**VPS1 tokens** (already installed on 161.248.81.138):\n- AHVHOLDING_API_KEY: `sk-3d8edc47e4037bc4-w85g8t-b82baf0b`\n- GITLAB_TOKEN: `glpat-rjgwaQjEp7hL_skbf8lXamM6MQpvOjEKdTpsNWJ5Zw8.01.171o9yg1e`\n- TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN: `8605080868:AAFFvDZs3YwWfxaLgW7Lgj42ANwyFIzmFT8` (@tieuvydev_bot)\n- STITCH_API_KEY: `AQ.Ab8RN6KimOxDQ4kNCgR68MBTO9qonEhjKMoCfu744Y4dWUblAg`\n- CONFLUENCE_URL: `https://dtlx.atlassian.net/wiki`\n- CONFLUENCE_EMAIL: `dqcuong.work@gmail.com`\n- CONFLUENCE_TOKEN: `ATATT3xFfGF03z7i01Hgl_4UzecsdxxBKCs10EFmrVwCmT1zeLPRxhkOKMv5eIqgKbTWPdTISeYkx7YdcdBkDy9_sduO2Rlu95A6XHfnFL3efXUCqva3JyFNVFAoFIYGqSX_Jvw4oc7JOaVVEjfpZhRd3DebLI_93JjEOGcliM_alSWdh01RY9c=44ED3599`\n\n**VPS2 tokens** (provided by user, not yet installed on 103.253.21.137):\n- IP: `103.253.21.137`, SSH attempt failed\n- TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN: `8302084207:AAF0hosICggXzqWbbXg2m76qt31Bl5EVj84`\n- GITLAB_TOKEN: `OPE3ObH44XLZsZoO0sqOD2M6MQpvOjEKdTpoYWpmcw8.01.17154spg1`\n- CONFLUENCE_URL: `https://dtlx.atlassian.net/wiki/home`\n- CONFLUENCE_EMAIL: `mai.chien2001ahvholding@gmail.com`\n- CONFLUENCE_TOKEN: `ATATT3xFfGF0CxCuoX9nAtFLkR-fjan_InPCO5qsXv6Ki2alKM3EmoD4-VcNuUM9aNBdlfxilLiV1Kzm9oVtM6PYo27j2OuEshJbLbNTFdBDIki-65Q7kHfks8DoAFJgqwfYYROPy2tQ0Qe9bmrZp9T_Eh9g3xV9CkAPYbR_DCy9x2UXF30dK5M=F760387B`\n- AHVHOLDING_API_KEY: **NOT YET PROVIDED**\n\n**Config files**:\n- VPS1 config: `/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json` (28,281 bytes, valid JSON, 38 agents, no `routing` key, no `match` in agents)\n- VPS1 startup: `/root/start-openclaw.sh` (sets all env vars + runs `openclaw gateway start`)\n- VPS1 systemd: `/etc/systemd/system/openclaw-gateway.service`\n- VPS1 Gateway token: `vps2-83eaaf256ae54e4fa1bf7798033cfe591438bcdff21417b3`\n\n**Pairing command** (use SSH tunnel for VPS gateway):\n```bash\n# Set up tunnel on local port 18799\nsshpass -p '<vps_pass>' ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no -L 18799:127.0.0.1:18789 root@161.248.81.138 'sleep 55' &\nsleep 3\n# Then approve with env var pointing to tunnel\nOPENCLAW_GATEWAY_PORT=18799 timeout 30 openclaw pairing approve telegram <CODE>\n```\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Original Request\nUser sent an SSH password (`38afG1FL!D5o[k`) for VPS `103.253.21.137` (root) — the assistant was to set up OpenClaw on this VPS.\n\n## Early Progress\n- **SSH handled via `expect`** to bypass shell special-char interpretation of the `!` and `[` in the password\n- **VPS already had OpenClaw** installed + running since 2026-04-16 (old tokens: `sk-3d8edc47e4037bc4-w85g8t-sr8yu3-2f0dda21`)\n- **Config uploaded** (`/tmp/openclaw-vps2-clean.json`) and tokens injected via Python script (`update_config.py`) — replacing AHV, GitLab (`glpat-OPE3ObH44...`), Telegram (`8302084207:AAF0...`), Stitch, and Confluence credentials\n- **Systemd service `openclaw-gateway`** updated and reloaded; old PIDs killed and service restarted\n\n## Context for Suffix\n- Gateway reached **READY state**: `ready (6 plugins: telegram; 13.1s)`\n- Port **18789 listening** on `127.0.0.1:18789`\n- Telegram bot: `@openclawsdjkfbsdjkf_bot` — verified working (GET `/getMe` returned `ok: true`)\n- Telegram has IPv4-only fallback mode active (network limitation on VPS)\n- **Next step in suffix:** User needs to open Telegram, message `@openclawsdjkfbsdjkf_bot`, send `/start` or `/pair`, and give the pairing code back to the assistant\n\n<read-files>\n/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/SOUL.md\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/USER.md\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/memory/2026-04-21.md\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/tmp/openclaw-vps2-fixed.json\n/tmp/openclaw-vps2.json\n/tmp/setup-vps3.sh\n/tmp/update_config.py\n</modified-files>","firstKeptEntryId":"3835dccb","tokensBefore":149334,"details":{"readFiles":["/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json","/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/SOUL.md","/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/USER.md","/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/memory/2026-04-21.md"],"modifiedFiles":["/tmp/openclaw-vps2-fixed.json","/tmp/openclaw-vps2.json","/tmp/setup-vps3.sh","/tmp/update_config.py"]},"fromHook":false}
