{"type":"message","id":"218a45eb","parentId":"098a3777","timestamp":"2026-04-21T07:30:33.450Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is resending the Confluence credentials. The issue on VPS 161.248.81.140 is that there are multiple openclaw processes competing for the port, causing the gateway to fail to start properly. The log shows \"already running under systemd\" over and over, which means the new process starts, finds the lock file, and exits - while the old process is still running.\n\nLet me take a more aggressive approach:\n1. First, kill ALL openclaw processes\n2. Delete lock files\n3. Start fresh\n\nThe issue is that `systemctl stop` doesn't work well because there are orphaned processes. Let me try a different approach.","thinkingSignature":"a0ffd9aed5b7e39ae7ebf4ca52f3005f419dfe41455c5476473be98dcf5a5500"},{"type":"text","text":"Xóa log cũ + kill toàn bộ process + restart:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_154r0mqxsiuv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"expect -c '\nspawn ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no root@161.248.81.140 \"ps aux | grep openclaw | grep -v grep | awk '{print \\$2}' | xargs kill -9 2>/dev/null; sleep 2; ps aux | grep openclaw | grep -v grep || echo CLEAN\"\nexpect \"password:\"\nsend \"qOY)9Ym242jIv.\\r\"\nexpect eof\n' 2>&1 | grep -v \"^spawn\\|^Password\"","timeout":20}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":1353,"output":293,"cacheRead":15883,"cacheWrite":30244,"totalTokens":47773,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776756620722,"responseId":"06365a8d20728d7ec3789cb1cf846156"}}
