{"type":"message","id":"b1ad6c53","parentId":"29a7e8ff","timestamp":"2026-04-21T07:35:43.868Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see it clearly. The systemd service is running as PID 324591 (openclaw) with a child PID 324600 (openclaw-gateway). The openclaw-gateway (PID 324600) is repeatedly saying \"already running under systemd; waiting 5000ms before retrying startup\".\n\nThis means the openclaw-gateway process (324600) is checking if there's already a gateway running on the port, and finding it itself (because it itself started the actual gateway). This is a bug in the openclaw startup where it checks for an existing gateway and finds itself.\n\nWait, actually this might be because the child process (324600) is the actual gateway, and it's checking if there's another gateway already running. \n\nSo the parent process (324591) is spawning the child (324600) to run the gateway, but then the child is incorrectly detecting that a gateway is already running and continuously retrying. Looking at the PID history, I killed off the old instances around 07:33, and the new ones started at 07:33:47, but now the child process is stuck in this retry loop.\n\nThe issue is that openclaw-gateway is a long-running process that forks itself, and systemd is tracking the parent (324591) while the child (324600) gets stuck believing another gateway instance is already running on the port. The warning messages show the child keeps retrying every 5 seconds, which is the expected behavior when it can't bind to the port because something else already has it. might be a bug where the child process keeps retrying instead of exiting when it can't bind to the port. But looking at the port status, PID 324600 is actually listening on 18789, so the gateway did start successfully despite those warning messages.\n\nThese repeated warnings are just noise from the child process—maybe a timing issue or a bug in how OpenClaw handles the fork. The real question is whether the gateway is actually functioning, which I can verify by making an HTTP request to it.","thinkingSignature":"1611d9c22ba153621d50e30e8d295dcd5e130e1485498bf626e0b7515b25374d"},{"type":"text","text":"Gateway đang chạy ✅ dù có spam log. Verify HTTP:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9uzst8fr4v8r_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"expect -c '\nspawn ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no root@161.248.81.140 \"curl -s http://127.0.0.1:18789/ | head -3\"\nexpect \"password:\"\nsend \"qOY)9Ym242jIv.\\r\"\nexpect eof\n' 2>&1 | grep -v \"^spawn\\|^Password\"","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":802,"output":543,"cacheRead":54455,"cacheWrite":521,"totalTokens":56321,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776756925950,"responseId":"06365bbf7a3f4dce759e4a3d0ea94c9c"}}
