{"type":"message","id":"2cb5948d","parentId":"9c4062c2","timestamp":"2026-04-21T07:36:23.202Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No confluence entries in the log. Let me check if the mcp config is correct and if the confluence MCP server is installed properly. Let me also check what the log says about MCP servers.\n\nActually, I realize the issue. The log file was cleared earlier, but the processes that were killed kept writing to the same file (because the file was just truncated but the file descriptor was still open by those processes). The NEW processes started after the log was cleared should have fresh logs. But there are no confluence entries.\n\nLet me check the latest log entries from the new process (324600) specifically.","thinkingSignature":"f98185ab4ba78adbe53c022020bec050b93046e77b6ecc92d2ab119f530148b2"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_165vds2oapvb_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"expect -c '\nspawn ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no root@161.248.81.140 \"grep -E '\\''mcp|plugin|ready'\\'' /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-04-21.log | tail -10\"\nexpect \"password:\"\nsend \"qOY)9Ym242jIv.\\r\"\nexpect eof\n' 2>&1 | grep -v \"^spawn\\|^Password\"","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":100,"output":244,"cacheRead":56296,"cacheWrite":300,"totalTokens":56940,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776756973907,"responseId":"06365befaba933355b2da964f0666125"}}
