{"type":"message","id":"eab3596d","parentId":"3835f4a8","timestamp":"2026-04-21T07:36:51.666Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No MCP entries at all. The log only shows the \"already running\" warnings. The actual startup messages (like \"loading configuration\", \"loaded N agents\", \"MCP servers\", etc.) are not appearing. This is very strange.\n\nWait - the log file was opened by the OLD processes (before the kill), and when I truncated it with `> /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-04-21.log`, the old processes were still writing to the same file (they had the file descriptor open). The NEW process (started after the truncate) should have created a new log file or the same file. But since the file was truncated (just emptied), the new process writes to the same file.\n \nBut here's the puzzle: the new process is emitting those \"already running\" warnings, which are legitimate messages, yet there's no \"loading configuration\" or \"MCP servers\" entries from it. The old processes were killed after the truncate, so they shouldn't be writing anymore. Could the new process be forked from the old one and inheriting its file descriptors?\n\nActually, that doesn't make sense either since the parent was killed. Let me reconsider—the new log entries showing \"already running\" are from the new process, so where are the startup messages? Maybe the configuration load happens before the \"already running\" check, and since the process detects it's already running, it skips the full initialization and goes straight to the retry loop. Or perhaps the log file was actually replaced with a new inode when I truncated it with `echo >`, so the old file descriptors became invalid and the new process is writing somewhere else entirely. I need to verify whether the Confluence configuration is actually present in the config file.","thinkingSignature":"fa441ff95436247cf7bd720396f233ae1d2c4e20124d7e1029e6273f4fc654ad"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vckgz20elrnr_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"expect -c '\nspawn ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no root@161.248.81.140 \"python3 -c \\\"import json; d=json.load(open('\\''/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json'\\'')); print('\\\\\\nmcp servers:', list(d.get('mcp',{}).get('servers',{}).keys()))\\\"\"\nexpect \"password:\"\nsend \"qOY)9Ym242jIv.\\r\"\nexpect eof\n' 2>&1 | grep -v \"^spawn\\|^Password\"","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":738,"output":491,"cacheRead":56629,"cacheWrite":353,"totalTokens":58211,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776756996670,"responseId":"06365c05169a141b3626e62a865dae5a"}}
