{"type":"message","id":"c49862b7","parentId":"17c09ef8","timestamp":"2026-04-21T07:37:39.978Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Confluence MCP server is configured correctly. The issue is that the gateway is not loading the MCP servers properly. Let me look at the journalctl logs from the very beginning of the process start to see what happened.Actually, the issue might be that the openclaw-gateway process (PID 324600) IS the actual gateway but it's stuck in a retry loop because it can't properly start. The \"already running\" messages suggest it keeps finding something on the port.\n\nBut the port IS listening. And curl IS working. So the gateway IS running. The issue is just that the child process (which is the one that shows \"already running under systemd\") is NOT the actual gateway process - it's a starter process that checks for an existing gateway.\n \nSo there's a parent-child relationship here: the main openclaw process spawns a child that attempts to bind to the port, and if it finds the port already in use, it logs that warning and exits. But the actual gateway is the grandchild process that's successfully listening on the port. Let me trace back through the process tree to confirm which PID is actually handling the requests.","thinkingSignature":"059e0a2a57ba2eec74765d8672219a76a64d17357c213271b8540cb2db3c9323"},{"type":"text","text":"Confluence MCP config OK ✅. Verify thực sự hoạt động:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xsgvdprm557c_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"expect -c '\nspawn ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no root@161.248.81.140 \"curl -s http://127.0.0.1:18789/api/mcp/servers 2>/dev/null | python3 -m json.tool 2>/dev/null | head -20\"\nexpect \"password:\"\nsend \"qOY)9Ym242jIv.\\r\"\nexpect eof\n' 2>&1 | grep -v \"^spawn\\|^Password\"","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":196,"output":382,"cacheRead":58367,"cacheW