{"type":"message","id":"05636c4f","parentId":"b6eab2b5","timestamp":"2026-04-21T07:38:22.389Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The gateway IS responding with HTTP 200 and proper headers. It's serving the OpenClaw control UI. The Confluence MCP should be available.\n\nThe issue with the log not showing confluence entries might be because:\n1. The MCP server section doesn't log on startup\n2. The log was cleared and only the \"retry\" messages are being written to it\n\nActually, I think the Confluence MCP IS working. Let me verify by checking if the confluence server.js is actually executable and has the right env vars set.\n\nLet me also check the journalctl logs to see the original startup messages.","thinkingSignature":"51b699c8cf2db56ec9a10653527f2a1eb70cbe45c00ee8d0bb612987a9aa5e28"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_c953f41kx6q5_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"expect -c '\nspawn ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no root@161.248.81.140 \"journalctl -u openclaw-gateway --no-pager -n 50 | grep -E '\\''mcp|conflu|ready|loading'\\'' -i | tail -20\"\nexpect \"password:\"\nsend \"qOY)9Ym242jIv.\\r\"\nexpect eof\n' 2>&1 | grep -v \"^spawn\\|^Password\"","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":450,"output":250,"cacheRead":59296,"cacheWrite":233,"totalTokens":60229,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776757094244,"responseId":"06365c674481b69645796a67a50f60f1"}}
