{"type":"message","id":"f716b645","parentId":"bed21762","timestamp":"2026-04-21T07:39:36.629Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see three processes:\n1. PID 324512 - `openclaw-gateway` (the one actually listening on port 18789)\n2. PID 324591 - `openclaw` (systemd main process)\n3. PID 324600 - `openclaw-gateway` (a child that's retrying)So PID 324512 is the actual gateway that's running. PIDs 324591 and 324600 are additional processes that were spawned somehow.\n\nThe issue is that the systemctl service seems to be spawning multiple processes. Let me check if there's a lock file issue causing double-spawn.Actually, looking at this more carefully: - PID 324512 is `openclaw-gateway` - listening on port 18789\n\n\n- PID 324600 is `openclaw-gateway` - NOT listening (the retry process)\n\nSo the service is definitely spawning duplicate gateway processes, which shouldn't be happening. I need to trace back through the earlier systemctl status output to figure out when the service was first started and why it's creating multiple instances.\n\nLooking at the timeline, the parent process (324591) was spawned at 07:33:47, and the child (324600) at 07:33:47 as well, which means systemd launched both simultaneously. This points to either a fork in the startup sequence or possibly the service restarting due to a crash. Let me check if there's a watchdog timer triggering repeated restarts, or if the service definition itself is misconfigured with Type=forking instead of Type=simple.\n\nActually, I think I've got it—the openclaw binary probably forks itself when starting the gateway, which is standard behavior, but systemd's waiting for the original process to exit rather than tracking the child that's actually running. That would explain why the service appears to be failing even though the gateway is up and running fine. I need to verify whether the Confluence MCP is actually working by checking the processes on the VPS—specifically, I should look for the confluence server process to confirm it's running as a subprocess of the gateway.","thinkingSignature":"5f7181c17b28535e8f889f0f78393e5dc915197d72c677ffe90a70e339913b1c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rdw78a15ndj6_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"expect -c '\nspawn ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no root@161.248.81.140 \"ps aux | grep -E '\\''node|conflu'\\'' | grep -v grep | head -10\"\nexpect \"password:\"\nsend \"qOY)9Ym242jIv.\\r\"\nexpect eof\n' 2>&1 | grep -v \"^spawn\\|^Password\"","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":219,"output":531,"cacheRead":61021,"cacheWrite":1468,"totalTokens":63239,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776757159685,"responseId":"06365ca8beea02d7e1de39ae924004af"}}
