{"type":"message","id":"e163eca8","parentId":"f772798d","timestamp":"2026-04-21T08:05:53.332Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see - the agents section on the VPS only has `defaults` and is missing the `list`. The issue is that when I uploaded the config, the Python update script I ran only updated the `env` and `mcp` sections but didn't properly handle the agents section. Let me look at the local config structure vs what was uploaded.\n\nWait, looking at the update script:\n```python\nwith open('/tmp/openclaw-vps5.json', 'w') as f:\n    json.dump(config, f, indent=2)\n```\n\nThis takes the base config and adds env + mcp. But the base config IS the full 38-agent config from openclaw-vps2-clean.json. \n\nSo the local VPS5 file should have all 38 agents. But when I checked the remote VPS 141, it only shows `defaults`. That means either the upload didn't actually replace the file, or the update script pulled from a different source than expected. Let me verify what the update script is actually using as its base.","thinkingSignature":"24865e207a71cf5d9e3343dcbd34ff8e3c8f93d53d050cd24e4d357f57de00cd"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_a6sfj5wvpiyt_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"expect -c '\nspawn ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no root@161.248.81.141 \"python3 -c \\\"import json; d=json.load(open('/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json')); print(len(d.get('agents',{}).get('list',[])))\\\"\"\nexpect \"password:\"\nsend \"m-@955nhAJ3lJK\\r\"\nexpect eof\n' 2>&1 | grep -v \"^spawn\\|^Password\"","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":221,"output":341,"cacheRead":76255,"cacheWrite":291,"totalTokens":77108,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776758742172,"responseId":"063662d7e4cc7efbc520c4f03933f265"}}
