{"type":"message","id":"6eb65e12","parentId":"15c7d1b2","timestamp":"2026-04-21T09:16:35.581Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait - I need to think about which VPS has which token. VPS 140 was set up with:\n- AHV: sk-3d8edc47e4037bc4-en4js2-0a5bcb88\n- Telegram: 8573023381:AAEzfQLMFz73iEA9pKEZz1CCM7RZF57vPmc (Dr0204_Luna_bot)\n- Confluence MCP (old creds)\n- Stitch was NOT added (skipped)\n\nBut wait, I also uploaded the full openclaw-vps5.json config to VPS 140, which had:\n\n\n- AHV: sk-3d8edc47e4037bc4-8cqz7x-9e68394f\n- Telegram: 8666593535:AAFtzIUyKYaGPVbhsyOaLN2MwFhW89o1-7Q (dyxuni_bot)\n- Confluence MCP with new creds\n\nSo the issue is that VPS 140 got overwritten with the wrong config at some point, mixing tokens from different sources.\n\nNow I'm realizing VPS 140 actually ended up with the wrong Telegram bot token entirely—it has Dr0204_Luna_bot (8573023381:AAEzfQLMFz73iEA9pKEZz1CCM7RZF57vPmc) from the user's original message, but that's not the correct token. The real issue is that the bot token was revoked, so I need to update VPS 140 with the new token from the user and then restart the gateway to apply the changes.","thinkingSignature":"0ce872cf5bac9769c77756117ce270b881f6f4bc154fe6615705c1cff22899de"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4gt01qas1560_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"expect -c '\nspawn scp -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no /tmp/update_token140.sh root@161.248.81.140:/tmp/update.sh\nexpect \"password:\"\nsend \"qOY)9Ym242jIv.\\r\"\nexpect eof\n' 2>&1 | tail -1 && echo \"---\" && expect -c '\nspawn ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no root@161.248.81.140 \"bash /tmp/update.sh\"\nexpect \"password:\"\nsend \"qOY)9Ym242jIv.\\r\"\nexpect eof\n' 2>&1 | grep -v \"^spawn\\|^Password\"","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":90,"output":503,"cacheRead":113243,"cacheWrite":430,"totalTokens":114266,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRe