{"type":"message","id":"e83a2b2e","parentId":"39a4a200","timestamp":"2026-04-21T11:40:46.329Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. The `agents.list` has 3 more broken entries after the already-fixed `article-writing`:\n1. `content-engine` (lines 947-970)\n2. `deep-research` (lines 971-996)\n3. `documentation-lookup` (lines 997-???)\n\nAnd the `subagents.allowAgents` array has broken entries too. \n\nThe `subagents.allowAgents` array issue is that:\n- Line 70: `'      \"subagents\": {\\n'` - opening brace, but no opening bracket for `allowAgents`\n- Line 71: `'        \"allowAgents\": [\\n'` - actually this looks correct\n\n\n- The problem is that `content-engine`, `deep-research`, `documentation-lookup`, and `article-writing` shouldn't be in `allowAgents` since they're deleted agents, and `typescript-reviewer` has a line formatting issue that broke the array structure.\n\nI need to remove those four entries from the `allowAgents` array and fix the indentation on `typescript-reviewer`. Let me check what comes after line 109 to see if there's a closing bracket for the array.","thinkingSignature":"50ea591552e72c89aa749883ce0086722572994417e1c5b78a8f7737532642a3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bmxw5i6idfvv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nwith open('/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json') as f:\n    lines = f.readlines()\nprint(f'Total lines: {len(lines)}')\nfor i, l in enumerate(lines[1005:1020], 1006):\n    print(f'{i}: {repr(l[:100])}')\n\"","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":992,"output":341,"cacheRead":123664,"cacheWrite":845,"totalTokens":125842,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776771637891,"responseId":"063695370c42149d237602281957a218"}}
{"type":"message","id":"431cc3b2","parentId":"e83a2b2e","timestamp":"2026-04-21T11:40:46.421Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_bmxw5i6idfvv_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Total lines: 2044\n1006: '        \"tools\": {\\n'\n1007: '          \"alsoAllow\": [\\n'\n1008: '            \"browser\",\\n'\n1009: '            \"agents_list\",\\n'\n1010: '            \"tts\",\\n'\n1011: '            \"memory_search\",\\n'\n1012: '            \"memory_get\",\\n'\n1013: '            \"sessions_list\",\\n'\n1014: '            \"sessions_history\",\\n'\n1015: '            \"sessions_send\",\\n'\n1016: '            \"sessions_spawn\",\\n'\n1017: '            \"subagents\"\\n'\n1018: '          ]\\n'\n1019: '        }\\n'\n1020: '      }\\n'"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":67,"aggregated":"Total lines: 2044\n1006: '        \"tools\": {\\n'\n1007: '          \"alsoAllow\": [\\n'\n1008: '            \"browser\",\\n'\n1009: '            \"agents_list\",\\n'\n1010: '            \"tts\",\\n'\n1011: '            \"memory_search\",\\n'\n1012: '            \"memory_get\",\\n'\n1013: '            \"sessions_list\",\\n'\n1014: '            \"sessions_history\",\\n'\n1015: '            \"sessions_send\",\\n'\n1016: '            \"sessions_spawn\",\\n'\n1017: '            \"subagents\"\\n'\n1018: '          ]\\n'\n1019: '        }\\n'\n1020: '      }\\n'","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776771646410}}
{"type":"message","id":"58c322ca","parentId":"431cc3b2","timestamp":"2026-04-21T11:41:09.911Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so the `documentation-lookup` entry ends at line 1020. Let me now check the subagents.allowAgents array more carefully. Looking at lines 70-109:\n\n- Line 70: `      \"subagents\": {\\n` - opens an object\n- Line 71: `        \"allowAgents\": [\\n` - opens the array correctly\n- Lines 72-108: agent names\n- Line 109: `        ],\\n` - closes the array\n\nThe issue is that `content-engine` (line 77) and `typescript-reviewer` (line 106) have issues in their formatting. \n\nLet me trace through the indentation more carefully. Line 106 has extra spaces before the content, which means it's malformed. The bigger problem is that `content-engine`, `deep-research`, `documentation-lookup`, and `article-writing` are all in the `allowAgents` list but they're also standalone agents with their own workspace definitions, and some of these entries have corrupted formatting. I need to write a Python script to systematically fix these issues rather than manually editing each line. I'm seeing that the issue spans the entire `subagents` block—`content-engine` has 14 spaces instead of 8, and `typescript-reviewer` has 22 spaces, making it look like a continuation of the previous line. I need to write a Python script to systematically fix this malformed section rather than patching individual lines.","thinkingSignature":"63c0a9e05b4b5751b324db2786693af2a3c0ea274b19f2ba8dac9986fe6632b9"},{"type":"text","text":"File local có nhiều chỗ break. Viết script fix toàn diện:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fkzla674bpbe_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/fix_local_json.py","content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\nimport json, re\n\nwith open('/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json', 'r') as f:\n    content = f.read()\n\n# Fix 1: subagents.allowAgents array - remove deleted agents, fix indentation\n# The subagents block starts with '\"subagents\": {' and contains allowAgents\n# Replace the whole subagents block with clean version\nsubagents_old = content[content.find('\"subagents\": {'):content.find('\"subagents\": {')+2000]\n\n# Build clean subagents.allowAgents - only existing agents\nALLOWED = [\n    'agile-product-owner', 'ai-seo', 'clean-code', 'code-reviewer',\n    'coding-standards', 'content-strategy', 'database-reviewer',\n    'database-schema-designer', 'epic-design', 'harness-optimizer',\n    'market-intelligence', 'master-orchestrator', 'performance-optimizer',\n    'planner', 'playwright-pro', 'product-marketing-context',\n    'product-strategy', 'prompt-optimizer', 'realistic-seeder',\n    'refactor-cleaner', 'security-reviewer', 'senior-architect',\n    'senior-backend', 'senior-devops', 'senior-frontend', 'senior-qa',\n    'senior-security', 'seo-audit', 'shadcn-expert', 'stitch-design',\n    'stitch-loop', 'typescript-reviewer', 'ui-design-system', 'ui-ux-pro-max'\n]\n\nclean_subagents = '      \"subagents\": {\\n        \"allowAgents\": [\\n'\nfor name in ALLOWED:\n    clean_subagents += f'          \"{name}\",\\n'\nclean_subagents += '        ]\\n      },'\n\n# Find and replace subagents block\nstart = content.find('\"subagents\": {')\nend = content.find('      },', start) + len('      },')\ncontent = content[:start] + clean_subagents + content[end:]\n\n# Fix 2: Remove content-engine, deep-research, documentation-lookup agent entries from agents.list\n# These entries are truncated/malformed\nfor bad in ['content-engine', 'deep-research', 'documentation-lookup']:\n    # Find the start of this agent entry\n    idx = content.find(f'\"id\": \"{bad}\"')\n    if idx >= 0:\n        # Find the opening { before this\n        start_idx = content.rfind('{', 0, idx)\n        # Find the closing } after this by counting braces\n        depth = 0\n        end_idx = start_idx\n        for i in range(start_idx, len(content)):\n            if content[i] == '{':\n                depth += 1\n            elif content[i] == '}':\n                depth -= 1\n                if depth == 0:\n                    end_idx = i + 1\n                    break\n        # Remove the entry (including trailing comma/newline)\n        removed = content[start_idx:end_idx]\n        # Find if there's a comma after\n        rest = content[end_idx:]\n        if rest.startswith(','):\n            end_idx += 1\n        content = content[:start_idx] + content[end_idx:]\n        print(f'Removed: {bad}')\n\n# Fix 3: Remove article-writing from agents.list (if still there, was already partially removed)\nidx = content.find('\"id\": \"article-writing\"')\nif idx >= 0:\n    start_idx = content.rfind('{', 0, idx)\n    depth = 0\n    end_idx = start_idx\n    for i in range(start_idx, len(content)):\n        if content[i] == '{': depth += 1\n        elif content[i] == '}':\n            depth -= 1\n            if depth == 0:\n                end_idx = i + 1\n                break\n    # Check if trailing comma\n    if content[end_idx:end_idx+1] == ',':\n        end_idx += 1\n    content = content[:start_idx] + content[end_idx:]\n    print('Removed: article-writing')\n\n# Now validate JSON\ntry:\n    d = json.loads(content)\n    print(f'JSON valid! agents in list: {len(d.get(\"agents\",{}).get(\"list\",[]))}')\n    mcp = d.get('mcp', {})\n    print(f'MCP config: {json.dumps(mcp, indent=2)}')\n    with open('/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json', 'w') as f:\n        json.dump(d, f, indent=2)\n    print('Saved.')\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f'Error: {e}')\n    # Save anyway\n    with open('/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json', 'w') as f:\n        f.write(content)\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":251,"output":1363,"cacheRead":124192,"cacheWrite":1588,"totalTokens":127394,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776771646438,"responseId":"0636953f6a1a666ec8ae7458