{"type":"message","id":"ac19b58a","parentId":"8899b33f","timestamp":"2026-04-21T11:43:39.420Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, the structure looks perfect! All the indentation is correct. `subagents` at 6 spaces, `allowAgents` at 8 spaces, items at 10 spaces, close `]` at 8 spaces, close `subagents` at 6 spaces.\n\nBut JSON parsing fails. Let me check if the problem is earlier in the file - maybe the `workspaces` array or something else before this section is broken.\n\nActually, wait. Let me check what happened to the original `workspaces` array. Earlier I found it started around line 82 (in the original file before the fix). After the cleanup, the `workspaces` array was removed. \n\nI need to verify whether the `workspaces` key still exists anywhere in the file, or if it got completely stripped out during the cleanup.","thinkingSignature":"19cc2b5f1e3185738c19d6f691852da7d13295be181480a52160bc15e09442be"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4xtqbwq75g6r_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nwith open('/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json') as f:\n    content = f.read()\n\n# Check for the word \"workspaces\" \nidx = content.find('\"workspaces\"')\nif idx >= 0:\n    print(f'Found workspaces at char {idx}')\n    print('Context:', repr(content[idx-20:idx+100]))\nelse:\n    print('No \"workspaces\" found')\n\n# Also check for the malformed article-writing issue from earlier\n# Let me look at the MCP section\nmcp_idx = content.find('\"mcp\"')\nprint(f'\\nMCP at char {mcp_idx}')\nprint('Context:', repr(content[mcp_idx:mcp_idx+200]))\nPYEOF","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":657,"output":356,"cacheRead":133698,"cacheWrite":1044,"totalTokens":135755,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776771809650,"responseId":"063695e31bb8995fe1aa9cf0a31e881b"}}
