{"type":"message","id":"19c6daf7","parentId":"3fdd4523","timestamp":"2026-04-21T11:44:14.055Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The VPS 141 config is valid with 34 agents. Let me use it as a base and add the local tokens/MCP configs. Let me check the local VPS 141 config vs the local config:- VPS 141 has the correct tokens for that VPS\n- Local has the AHV API key for local machine\n\nLet me:1. Use the VPS 141 config as base\n2. Update the tokens (AHV, Telegram, Confluence) for local machine\n3. Check if MCP confluence is in the local file","thinkingSignature":"f53897a49f95ffa7ae6fd3e5ec91cf50166bde237da7cf629240c6b0c78dca8d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_28vp4r7hi7x4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport json\n\n# Load the valid VPS 141 config\nwith open('/tmp/openclaw-vps141.json') as f:\n    vps_config = json.load(f)\n\n# Load the broken local config to extract tokens/MCP\nwith open('/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json') as f:\n    try:\n        # Even if broken, we can read partial\n        pass\n    except:\n        pass\n\n# Read raw to find tokens\nwith open('/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json') as f:\n    raw = f.read()\n\n# Extract values via regex\nimport re\nahv_key = re.search(r'AHVHOLDING_API_KEY[\"\\s:=]+([\\w-]+)', raw)\n# Just use the VPS 141 config but update with local env vars\n\n# Update VPS 141 config with local AHV key\nvps_config['env']['AHVHOLDING_API_KEY'] = 'sk-3d8edc47e4037bc4-w85g8t-b82baf0b'\n\n# Check current Telegram token in VPS 141 config\nprint('VPS 141 TELEGRAM:', vps_config.get('channels', {}).get('telegram', {}).get('botToken', 'not found'))\nprint('VPS 141 AHV:', vps_config.get('env', {}).get('AHVHOLDING_API_KEY', 'not found'))\nprint('VPS 141 MCP:', list(vps_config.get('mcp', {}).get('servers', {}).keys()))\n\n# Save as new local config\nwith open('/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json', 'w') as f:\n    json.dump(vps_config, f, indent=2)\nprint('Saved.')\nPYEOF","timeo