{"type":"message","id":"30f2c668","parentId":"e94f07ff","timestamp":"2026-04-21T11:44:42.377Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The current config has no MCP servers and only AHV API key. The user wants to check why confluence MCP doesn't work on local. Let me add the confluence MCP config to the local machine, and then also add the other necessary env vars.\n\nActually wait - the user asked to \"check lại cấu hình hiện tại ở local tại sao mcp server của confluence lại không hoạt động\". This means they want to DEBUG why confluence MCP doesn't work on the local machine.\n\nLet me think about what could be wrong with confluence MCP on local:1. The `mcp` config might be missing or wrong2. The confluence server.js might not exist3. The env vars (CONFLUENCE_URL, EMAIL, TOKEN) might be wrong\n\n\nI need to add the confluence MCP configuration to the local machine since it's currently empty, and I should verify that all the required environment variables are properly set for it to function.","thinkingSignature":"48484ca3cc039e3e1b41543155ca6fdfa45e763c04e49d5a476a48bd3be38b54"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wwb8lpraev0w_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls /root/.openclaw/mcp-servers/confluence/server.js 2>/dev/null && echo \"EXISTS\" || echo \"MISSING\"","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":100,"output":265,"cacheRead":136820,"cacheWrite":861,"totalTokens":138046,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776771873541,"responseId":"0636962319b7d8b8788f2d7b63e0ce80"}}
