{"type":"message","id":"0d5ebe6b","parentId":"552dd600","timestamp":"2026-04-21T16:24:49.249Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue! There are TWO `openclaw-gateway` processes:\n- PID 598102 (gateway from 16:21)\n- PID 598141 (gateway from 16:22)\n\nThis is causing conflicts. Also there are TWO `openclaw-tui` processes (one from 15:39 with pts/0 terminal, and the running one from the current session).\n\nThe main issue is:\n1. Multiple gateway processes running simultaneously (ports conflict)\n2. The `spawn` command for agents tries to start a new agent but gets blocked by the gateway conflict\n\nLet me also check the IPv6/mDNS issue - bonjour is stuck in \"probing\" state because the machine has IPv6 but no proper mDNS support.\n \nThe \"gateway already running under systemd\" warning is actually telling me that the TUI is trying to start a new gateway instance, but the old one from 15:39 is still holding the port, so it's blocked. I need to clean up these zombie processes and restart everything cleanly.","thinkingSignature":"1fdc6eb3763ef93cf0146c2ec1d0b4f9ea3287bef911aa07e8e641aa464db1aa"},{"type":"text","text":"Tìm thấy nguyên nhân:\n\n**1. Nhiều gateway processes chạy cùng lúc:**\n- PID 596366 (từ 15:39 — TUI cũ)\n- PID 598102 (từ 16:21)\n- PID 598141 (từ 16:22 — vừa restart)\n- 2 confluence MCP node processes\n\n**2. Bonjour/mDNS stuck** — không resolve được, gateway name conflict liên tục\n\nKill hết và restart sạch:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nro55ilay5g6_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ps aux | grep openclaw | grep -v grep | awk '{print $2}' | xargs kill -9 2>/dev/null; sleep 2; ps aux | grep openclaw | grep -v grep | wc -l","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":463,"output":420,"cacheRead":143775,"cacheWrite":1194,"totalTokens":145852,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopRe