{"type":"message","id":"29e953cb","parentId":"4f23355f","timestamp":"2026-04-21T19:34:20.807Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The subagent is completely stuck - it's not responding to the wake-up message either. The session is effectively dead but the status might still show as running. The LLM idle timeout is preventing any new response.\n\nThe best solution would be to abort this session and restart it with a fresh context. But I need the master-orchestrator to do that, and the master-orchestrator itself is also overwhelmed.\n\nActually, looking at this more carefully - the master-orchestrator session itself is running with 43 child subagents. That's a LOT. The system might be resource-constrained. Let me check if there are enough resources.\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. The subagent is deadlocked waiting for model responses. \n\nThe real problem is that the subagent has accumulated too much context over many turns and is now hitting timeout limits when trying to process new requests. I need to restart the subagent to clear that context, but since it's a child of the master-orchestrator, I can't do that directly - I'd need to either have the master-orchestrator handle it or find another way to signal a fresh start. The real issue is that subagent is completely stuck and unresponsive to wake-up calls, so I need to escalate this to the master-orchestrator to abort and respawn it with a fresh context. But the master-orchestrator itself is managing 43 subagents and running low on resources, so I should check its token usage before attempting to send it a recovery signal. The real issue is that the subagent is stuck in a timeout loop because it's accumulated too much context from previous iterations. The best approach is to have the master-orchestrator abort the current session and spawn a fresh one with an explicit directive to avoid the pattern that's causing the bloat.","thinkingSignature":"73f9867b45bce94cc81cd32e01aa8581b01fe864521a4ae08a63d4edf1ad5842"},{"type":"text","text":"Subagent không respond được — context đã đầy, model treo. Master-orchestrator cũng đang quá tải với 43 subagents.\n\nSignal master-orchestrator abort subagent này:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6g8rjns4ha6e_1","name":"sessions_send","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","message":"CRITICAL: Subagent session 52f0c795-a0e6-4fbc-9372-fe4cf966a590 đang bị LLM idle timeout hoàn toàn. Abort session này ngay. Sau đó respawn fresh session cho task PPE Safety với directive: (1) dùng AHV-Holding-DEV model, (2) giữ context < 50K tokens mỗi turn, (3) không spawn quá 5 subagents cùng lúc. Report kết quả.","timeoutSeconds":45}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":151,"output":594,"cacheRead":154551,"cacheWrite":1107,"totalTokens":156403,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776800045319,"responseId":"0637042f8f9a3b5a1c76c27857813687"}}
{"type":"message","id":"de8b940e","parentId":"29e953cb","timestamp":"2026-04-21T19:35:08.409Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_6g8rjns4ha6e_1","toolName":"sessions_send","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"runId\": \"c16cb20c-ce70-4392-86de-dce8712dd53d\",\n  \"status\": \"timeout\",\n  \"sessionKey\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134\"\n}"}],"details":{"runId":"c16cb20c-ce70-4392-86de-dce8712dd53d","status":"timeout","sessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776800108403}}
{"type":"message","id":"31d91724","parentId":"de8b940e","timestamp":"2026-04-21T19:35:22.793Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Both the master-orchestrator and its subagent are not responding. The system is completely stuck. The master-orchestrator itself has 200K context tokens and is busy managing 43 subagents.\n\nThe fundamental issue is that the master-orchestrator's context is full (200K tokens) which means every operation takes extremely long or times out. This is a systemic problem with how the orchestrator is managing its conversation history.\n\nI need to tell the user what's happening and what the root causes are:\n1. Context bloat - master session at 200K tokens\n2. Too many concurrent subagents (43)\n3. Subagent using slow model (TroLy with 2486 token overhead per call)\n\n\n4. The master-orchestrator's conversation history with 43 active subagents is consuming all available context space, forcing every new operation to process through an extremely compressed context window that's causing the timeout cascade.","thinkingSignature":"9f043de386017f2fea0e269f836c3c1ff15dc7d6eb9cb5225bdd4ecd9256ca61"},{"type":"text","text":"**Tình trạng hệ thống:**\n\n| Vấn đề | Mức độ |\n|---|---|\n| Master-orchestrator context: **200K/200K tokens** (đầy) | 🔴 nghiêm trọng |\n| Concurrent subagents: **43 cái** đang chạy | 🔴 quá tải |\n| Subagent 52f0c795: **LLM idle timeout 60s** (không respond được) | 🔴 stuck |\n| Model `TroLy`: ~2486 tokens overhead/call (quá nặng) | 🟡 chậm |\n\n**Nguyên nhân gốc:** Context đầy 200K → mỗi LLM call phải xử lý lại toàn bộ context → timeout. Subagent không có buffer để tiếp tục.\n\n**Giải pháp cần làm:**\n1. Abort master-orchestrator session hiện tại (clear context)\n2. Giảm concurrent subagents xuống ≤5\n3. Tất cả agent dùng `AHV-Holding-DEV` thay vì `TroLy`\n\nBạn muốn tôi restart master-orchestrator session không?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":131,"output":473,"cacheRead":155152,"cacheWrite":1192,"totalTokens":156948,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776800108467,"responseId":"0637046e16983097b4d5c534a477f568"}}
